The paper discusses the verification of component and connector (C&C) models, which is a topic within software engineering. Therefore, cs.SE (Software Engineering) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also presents algorithms for decision-making, which could fall under cs.PL (Programming Languages) or cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The use of natural language texts suggests a possible connection to cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). Finally, the performance and scalability experiments could be related to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
